{"schema": {"fields":[{"type":"integer","name":"index"},{"type":"string","name":"author_association"},{"type":"string","name":"body"},{"type":"datetime","name":"created_at"},{"type":"string","name":"html_url"},{"type":"integer","name":"id"},{"type":"string","name":"issue_url"},{"type":"string","name":"node_id"},{"type":"datetime","name":"updated_at"},{"type":"string","name":"url"},{"type":"string","name":"user"}],"pandas_version":"0.20.0","primaryKey":["index"]}, "data": [{"index":0,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"> Is it possible to extend a shape from array of points or Vector3 instances?\r\n\r\nNo, you can't just pass in an array of points to `ExtrudeGeometry`. The implementation calls [Curve.computeFrenetFrames](https:\/\/threejs.org\/docs\/index.html#api\/extras\/core\/Curve.computeFrenetFrames) in order to calculate  correct extrusions along the curve. Use your points to create an instance of `CatmullRomCurve3` and apply this to `ExtrudeGeometry` as a parameter.","created_at":"2018-03-13T10:44:59.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13578#issuecomment-372622913","id":372622913,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13578","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM3MjYyMjkxMw==","updated_at":"2018-03-13T10:44:59.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/372622913","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/12612165?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/Mugen87","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyNjEyMTY1","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"Mugen87","type":"User","id":12612165,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/orgs"}},{"index":1,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"Please use the forum for help, instead. Thank you.\r\n\r\nThis may help: https:\/\/threejs.org\/examples\/webgl_geometry_extrude_shapes.html\r\n\r\nAlso, https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13553.","created_at":"2018-03-13T15:18:27.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13578#issuecomment-372702449","id":372702449,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13578","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM3MjcwMjQ0OQ==","updated_at":"2018-03-13T15:21:17.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/372702449","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":2,"author_association":"NONE","body":"@Mugen87 Thanks for the answer first. If I understand correctly, \"CatmullRomCurve3\" in Three, currently only accepts control points not the original points. To recover control points I need to perform some extra computation. Otherwise I have to change APIs to send data (sadly) in a different manner. Anyway, when I do all Splines computation in client side, it takes a lot of time (might be 3 to 5 seconds) to do that. \r\n\r\n@WestLangley Hi, I understand it. I am not trying to be boring you. But I think it is a feature and developers can help me fastly by making some modification of original codes ... (I have searched stackoverflow before)","created_at":"2018-03-14T04:28:38.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13578#issuecomment-372900983","id":372900983,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13578","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM3MjkwMDk4Mw==","updated_at":"2018-03-15T04:35:36.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/372900983","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yiakwy\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yiakwy\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/8510840?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yiakwy","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yiakwy\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/yiakwy","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yiakwy\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjg1MTA4NDA=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yiakwy\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yiakwy\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yiakwy\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"yiakwy","type":"User","id":8510840,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yiakwy\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yiakwy\/orgs"}},{"index":3,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"@yiakwy \r\n\r\nTry this:\r\n```javascript\r\n\/\/ Polyline3 class\r\n\r\nfunction Polyline3( points ) {\r\n\r\n\tTHREE.Curve.call( this );\r\n\r\n\t\/\/ points is an array of THREE.Vector3()\r\n\r\n\tthis.points = points;\r\n\r\n}\r\n\r\nPolyline3.prototype = Object.create( THREE.Curve.prototype );\r\nPolyline3.prototype.constructor = Polyline3;\r\n\r\n\/\/ define the getPoint function for the subClass\r\nPolyline3.prototype.getPoint = function ( t ) {\r\n\r\n\t\/\/ t is a float between 0 and 1\r\n\r\n\tvar points = this.points;\r\n\r\n\tvar d = ( points.length - 1 ) * t;\r\n\r\n\tvar index1 = Math.floor( d );\r\n\tvar index2 = ( index1 < points.length - 1 ) ? index1 + 1 : index1;\r\n\r\n\tvar pt1 = points[ index1 ];\r\n\tvar pt2 = points[ index2 ];\r\n\r\n\tvar weight = d - index1;\r\n\r\n\treturn new THREE.Vector3().copy( pt1 ).lerp( pt2, weight );\r\n\r\n};\r\n\r\nvar path = new Polyline3( points );\r\n```\r\n","created_at":"2018-03-14T17:02:43.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13578#issuecomment-373098465","id":373098465,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13578","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM3MzA5ODQ2NQ==","updated_at":"2018-03-14T17:02:43.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/373098465","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":4,"author_association":"NONE","body":"@WestLangley for es6 representation, I get the point that I need to override **getPoint** method so that ExtrudeGeometry can use it.\r\n\r\n```js\r\n\/* will be compiled by webpack with es6 loader *\/\r\nclass Polyline3D extends THREE.Curve {\r\n constructor(points) {\r\n  super()\r\n  this.points = points\r\n }\r\n\r\n find(u, t) {\r\n\/*Implement your line search algorithm*\/\r\n }\r\n\r\n  getPoint(t) {\r\n  \/\/ mapping f: [0, 1] -> Point3D\r\n  \/\/ it is better to use a mthod call find(u,t), where u is last position (we are increasing sequences)\r\n  \/\/ I used the same strategy for my de Boor toolkit when I need to extract bezier curve segments. It saves your searching time.  t >= u\r\n  \/\/ it is better that u is an observable proxy(get, set) so that it can detects whether it is overflow automatically.\r\n  this.u = this.find(this.u,t)\r\n  let w = t - u\r\n  let point = lerp1st(this.points[u], this.points[u+1], w)\r\n  return point\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nOne can consider to push the functionality into original codes by\r\n\r\n```js\r\nfunc CurveFactory () {\r\n  if (arguments[0].constructor === Array) {\r\n    return new Polyline3D(arguments[0])\r\n  } else {\r\n    return new THREE.Curve()\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```","created_at":"2018-03-15T05:49:18.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13578#issuecomment-373268193","id":373268193,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/13578","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM3MzI2ODE5Mw==","updated_at":"2018-08-12T13:48:16.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/373268193","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yiakwy\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yiakwy\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/8510840?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yiakwy","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yiakwy\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/yiakwy","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yiakwy\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjg1MTA4NDA=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yiakwy\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yiakwy\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yiakwy\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"yiakwy","type":"User","id":8510840,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yiakwy\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/yiakwy\/orgs"}}]}